xmlText.p: Death toll from Pakistan earthquake rises to 37 - local official
ISLAMABAD, Sept 25 (Reuters) - The death toll from an earthquake in Pakistan on Tuesday has risen to 37, the Mirpur divisional commissioner, Muhammad Tayyab, said on Wednesday.
Tayyab said the dead included men, women and children. (Reporting by Asif Shahzad in Islamabad; Editing by Toby Chopra)
